What's included
src/SwapExecutor.sol — the main contract covering all required features:

SwapRequest struct with status enum (Pending / Executed / Cancelled)
createSwapRequest() — payable, locks ETH, stores request on-chain
executeSwap() — calls Uniswap V2 Router with swapExactETHForTokens, sends USDC directly to the user
cancelSwapRequest() — refunds ETH to the owner
getUserSwapHistory() — full swap history per wallet
getExpectedUsdc() — read-only quote
Events, custom errors, ReentrancyGuard, slippage protection

test/SwapExecutor.t.sol — 12 tests covering happy paths, reverts, and a fuzz test
script/DeploySwapExecutor.s.sol — deploys to Sepolia with auto-verification in one command
script/ExecuteSwap.s.sol — quotes, creates, and executes a live 0.01 ETH → USDC swap




# 1. Install Foundry & dependencies
foundryup
forge install Uniswap/v2-periphery Uniswap/v2-core OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts

# 2. Fill in .env (copy from .env.example)

# 3. Run tests
forge test --fork-url $SEPOLIA_RPC_URL -vvv

# 4. Deploy + auto-verify
forge script script/DeploySwapExecutor.s.sol:DeploySwapExecutor \
  --$SEPOLIA_RPC_URL --broadcast --verify --etherscan-api-key $ETHERSCAN_API_KEY -vvvv

# 5. Execute a live swap (save the tx hash for submission)
EXECUTOR_ADDRESS=0x... forge script script/ExecuteSwap.s.sol:ExecuteSwap \
  --rpc-url sepolia --broadcast -vvvv